<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 7:57AM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Harnett,
northwestern Cumberland and southeastern Lee Counties through 830 AM
EST...
At 756 AM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Pope AFB, or 10 miles north of Fort Bragg, moving
northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rain may lead to isolated flooding in poor drainage
locations. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lillington, Fort Bragg, Dunn, Angier, Pope AFB, Spring Lake, Erwin,
Coats, Broadway and Linden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
